TEMPLATE: REPAIR DRAWING LAYOUT (DXF Format Placeholder)

This file would normally contain a DXF (Drawing Exchange Format) template for structural repair drawings.

A typical repair drawing includes:

1. TITLE BLOCK
   - Drawing Number
   - Revision
   - Aircraft Model/MSN
   - Repair Location
   - Engineer/Approver signatures
   - Date

2. GENERAL NOTES
   - Material specifications
   - Process specifications
   - Fastener torque values
   - Sealant application notes
   - NDT requirements

3. VIEWS (Multi-view orthographic projection)
   - Plan view (top view of repair area)
   - Section views (showing ply stacking sequence or doubler installation)
   - Detail views (enlarged views of critical features)

4. DIMENSIONS
   - Repair boundaries
   - Fastener spacing and edge distances
   - Scarf taper dimensions
   - Ply sizes (for composite repairs)

5. PARTS LIST / BILL OF MATERIALS
   - Fasteners (quantity, part number)
   - Doublers or patches (material, thickness)
   - Plies (material, orientation, quantity)
   - Sealants and adhesives

6. REFERENCE COORDINATE SYSTEM
   - Aircraft coordinate system (FS, BL, WL)
   - Datum references

7. ZONES AND SECTIONS
   - Section cut indicators (A-A, B-B, etc.)
   - Zone identifiers per aircraft structure manual

NOTES FOR IMPLEMENTATION:
- This template should be created in CAD software (e.g., AutoCAD, CATIA, Siemens NX)
- Exported to DXF format for interoperability
- Layer structure:
  - Layer 0: Geometry (repair outline, fastener locations)
  - Layer 1: Dimensions
  - Layer 2: Annotations and notes
  - Layer 3: Title block and borders
  - Layer 4: Reference datums

